 :tx/rationale "PROFOUND INSIGHT: Materialized views as Store fields — the daemon is NOT the performance fix. The real fix is maintaining F(S), coherence, task counts, M(t) as incremental accumulators inside the Store struct, updated by apply_tx alongside the existing 5 indexes. This makes all derived values O(1) reads and O(k) updates. The views are serialized in store.bin automatically (Serde). Even in embedded mode with cache miss, the views are rebuilt during from_datoms (same O(n) pass that builds indexes). No separate 29s compute_fitness pass ever needed again. The daemon STILL adds value: (1) eliminates 0.9s I/O via ArcSwap in-memory, (2) enables W_alpha for operational telemetry, (3) CRDT periodic sync for multi-agent. But the daemon is Phase 1 polish, not Phase 0 correctness. Phase 0 = MaterializedViews in Store. This is the axiologically correct factoring because it uses the system's own abstraction (materialized views, already used for LIVE index) rather than introducing external mechanisms (caching, daemons, background threads)."
